EVR - Market Data & News
EVR - Stock Valuation Report
 Trade 

Evercore Partners Inc Class A (EVR) traded on unusually high volume on Jul. 27, as the stock 
gained 0.76% to close at $79.20. On the day, Evercore Partners Inc Class A saw 843,108 shares trade hands on 6,517 trades. 
Considering that the stock averages only a daily volume of 407,929 shares a day over the last month, this represents a pretty significant bump in volume over the norm.

Generally speaking, when a stock experiences a sudden spike in trading volume, it may be seen as a bullish signal for investors. An increase in volume means more market awareness for the 
company, potentially setting up a more meaningful move in stock price. The added volume also provides a level of support and stability for price advances.

The stock has traded between $83.30 and $47.31 over the last 52-weeks, its 50-day SMA is now $71.45, and its 200-day SMA $70.74. Evercore Partners Inc Class A 
has a P/B ratio of 5.81. It also has a P/E ratio of 19.3.  


Evercore Partners Inc is an investment banking and investment management firm. It provides financial advisory services to clients on mergers, acquisitions, divestitures and other strategic corporate transactions.

Headquartered in New York, NY, Evercore Partners Inc Class A has 1,475 employees and is currently under the leadership of CEO Ralph L. Schlosstein.


For a complete fundamental analysis analysis of Evercore Partners Inc Class A, check out Equities.com’s Stock Valuation Analysis report 
for EVR.

